Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.29,0:00:05.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be a surprise\Nif you had perished in that battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.05,0:00:11.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I prioritized your healing,\Nand allowed you to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.38,0:00:14.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So that you could answer my questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.26,0:00:19.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're the witch we met\Nat Dimitrie's castle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.02,0:00:21.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What were you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.19,0:00:23.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is he to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.02,0:00:26.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you also trying\Nto bring about the Ultimate Chaos?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.61,0:00:33.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be talented\Nfor summoning demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.78,0:00:40.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Were you the one who summoned the Demon Lord\Nand triggered the Great Hall Tragedy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.62,0:00:46.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To murder the leaders of the Union and Alliance\Nright in the heart of Eramu...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.84,0:00:49.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you can do that by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.67,0:00:53.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible without the backing\Nof an organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.22,0:00:55.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.86,0:01:12.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.16,0:02:54.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Mage Academy has convicted the Black Witch,\NJana, of perpetrating the Great Hall Tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.84,0:03:01.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They've sent an envoy to execute her\Nhere in Sistina immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.26,0:03:02.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Execute?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.39,0:03:06.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, this would never happen\Nwithout a thorough investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.77,0:03:11.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What could the Academy be thinking?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.69,0:03:17.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In praise of Sir Theo Cornaro's achievements,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.65,0:03:21.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,as per Academy regulations,\Nwe grant him the court rank of Earl,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.32,0:03:26.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and officially recognize him\Nas the ruler of Sistina and Bulltava.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.83,0:03:31.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, we offer these rewards for\Nthe achievement of capturing the Black Witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.13,0:03:40.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.21,0:04:20.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's always the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.30,0:04:25.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody just uses me as much as they can,\Nand then they discard me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.97,0:04:29.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think that I'll die like you want me to!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.89,0:04:33.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I offer you my soul! Demon Lord Release!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.49,0:04:44.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is she summoning the Demon Lord by herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.72,0:05:04.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.63,0:05:06.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the Great Hall...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.97,0:05:09.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Tragedy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.27,0:05:15.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think this is over now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.56,0:05:20.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're all going to hell,\Nand I'll be waiting for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.04,0:05:41.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro has been recognized\Nby the Mage Academy as ruler of Sistina
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.34,0:05:44.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,for defeating the Rossini family\Nand capturing the Black Witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.47,0:05:47.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have no interest in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.72,0:05:52.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The only one we need to be wary of\Nis the king of Sievis, Lassic David.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:56.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Theo Cornaro, previously retainer\Nof the Forest of Eternal Darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.81,0:05:59.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is popular among the Altirk people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.65,0:06:04.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If word spreads that he liberated his homeland\Nof Sistina from the Rossinis' oppression,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.69,0:06:09.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the free Lords' current revolt\Nwill surely gain momentum.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.33,0:06:12.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to report, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.66,0:06:15.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The free Lords are assaulting our fortress!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:16.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.55,0:06:29.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With a force of 1,000 men in position,\Nhow could they only last for less than two days?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.43,0:06:34.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, they were surprise-attacked while\Nhalf the force was away on a diversionary mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.47,0:06:37.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told that there were witches\Nand werewolves among the enemy ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.35,0:06:41.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- Sir Milza?\N- What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.61,0:06:44.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is no longer a mere uprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.53,0:06:49.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We should assume that the citizens of Altirk\Nhave declared war on us as soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.32,0:06:51.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm well aware of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.41,0:06:55.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The question is,\Nwhy aren't my citizens obeying us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.16,0:06:59.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only exercising my legitimate right to rule\Nover them, according to the court rank system.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.83,0:07:01.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're absolutely right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.79,0:07:04.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Citizens must obey the will of their ruler.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.63,0:07:09.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Should they join forces with someone other\Nthan their ruler, that makes them our enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.88,0:07:12.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling me to kill my citizens?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.76,0:07:16.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that might be unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.69,0:07:21.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,True, it would doom\Nsome innocent citizens to die as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.77,0:07:27.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that blame should rest on those people\Nwho are using them as a front to revolt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.15,0:07:30.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please firm your resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.57,0:07:32.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Resolve, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.12,0:07:36.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take up that suggestion of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.45,0:07:39.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll be the one to decide where we attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.00,0:07:39.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.96,0:07:41.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll start with the White Witches' village.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.88,0:07:43.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After that, the Werewolves' village.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.00,0:07:47.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And finally the stronghold of the free Lords\Nwho attacked this fortress!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.59,0:07:51.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show my resolve to the citizens of Altirk!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.81,0:08:02.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This way! Hurry! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.10,0:08:05.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! Get inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.37,0:08:24.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was too deferential to Villar's people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.88,0:08:28.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From here on, I can go about\Ninvading Regalia with impunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.26,0:08:31.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope it will prove to be that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.88,0:08:35.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's proceeding exactly as you want it to,\Nso what's making you anxious?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.06,0:08:39.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That would be Theo Cornaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.93,0:08:43.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What if he returned to Altirk...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.06,0:08:45.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo's nothing special.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.81,0:08:50.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even in Sistina, all he did was incite the masses,\Nand after forcing them to make sacrifices,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.53,0:08:52.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he's complacently playing the hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.86,0:08:56.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir, if I may, that's exactly what it means\Nto strive for the king's path.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.53,0:08:58.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.08,0:09:04.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, your suggestion has opened my eyes\Nto the fact that my resolve is still lacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.58,0:09:08.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, I will mow down\Nanyone who stands in my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.75,0:09:14.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what kind of path I take,\NI shall never stop, nor turn back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.35,0:09:22.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.31,0:09:25.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our village must've been burned to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.48,0:09:30.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.32,0:09:33.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That young boy is coming back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.57,0:09:41.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A report came in that both the villages of\Nthe Werewolves and the White Witches
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.29,0:09:46.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,have been burned down by Prince Milza, and\Nthat all citizens who resisted have been purged.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.67,0:09:48.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.46,0:09:55.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I always knew that after battling the Rossini\Nfamily, my next opponent would be Milza.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.13,0:09:56.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be difficult to overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.22,0:10:01.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But unless I bring him down,\Nthe Treaty has no future.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.77,0:10:09.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So good to see you back!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.36,0:10:12.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.90,0:10:14.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And bravo on your conquest of Sistina!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.36,0:10:16.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Laura!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.53,0:10:19.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that you committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.12,0:10:23.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Helga's poison,\NI didn't get to die, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.91,0:10:28.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm serving Lady Eudokia now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.21,0:10:35.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo, during this conference,\NI'd like to ask to serve under you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.97,0:10:39.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind waiting just a little longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.05,0:10:41.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You sure know how to keep a guy in suspense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.60,0:10:45.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, since we first fought each other,\Nour positions have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.85,0:10:49.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When your court rank goes up,\Nit's just more toil and trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.94,0:10:51.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.86,0:11:00.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moreno?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.78,0:11:05.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be all right if I took the reins\Nduring this conference?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.12,0:11:09.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you take charge when\Nyou're not even the leader's mage,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.12,0:11:12.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it would be like proclaiming\Na change in leadership.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.59,0:11:17.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we are asking Sir Lassic to hold off\Non his request to serve Sir Theo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.26,0:11:22.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you want to show everyone that he does\Nintend to have Sir Lassic serve under him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.47,0:11:24.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.10,0:11:30.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'd tread carefully. There are still\Nquite a few Lords who resent Sir Theo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.81,0:11:35.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When they blame you guys for all the people\Nwho lost their lives while you were gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.23,0:11:38.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right. I'll be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.91,0:11:44.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, let us begin\Nthe Altirk Treaty Lords' Summit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.58,0:11:48.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- Siluca.\N- Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.37,0:11:51.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Before we start this conference,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.42,0:11:55.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to offer a moment of silence\Nfor the many Altirk Lords
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.92,0:11:59.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,who lost their lives\Nwhile I was away in Sistina.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.48,0:12:14.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.32,0:12:17.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.03,0:12:20.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What you achieved in Sistina\Nwas truly magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.95,0:12:25.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That said, it only makes me wish all the more\Nthat you'd remained on the Continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.16,0:12:28.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not so sure about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.12,0:12:31.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Sir Theo is to be held accountable\Nfor being absent,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.08,0:12:35.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then those of us who were here\Nhave even greater culpability.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.71,0:12:38.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not talking about culpability.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.09,0:12:42.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I merely wished to point out how great a blow\Nit was to not have the hero, Sir Theo, with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.05,0:12:47.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But despite being a Lord of this Treaty,\Nhis decision to prioritize the liberation
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.81,0:12:52.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,of his homeland over the war\Nwith the Alliance seems questionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.31,0:12:59.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than who's to blame, shouldn't we be\Ndiscussing the future of the Treaty right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.53,0:13:05.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But then, you do seem to be anxious about\Nwho the next leader will be, Sir Alfred!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.87,0:13:08.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Eudokia, do you have any views\Nthat you'd like to share?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.16,0:13:14.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I, for one, would prefer to have\NSir Lassic continue to lead the Treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.00,0:13:20.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Currently, my nation, Haman is under constant attack\Nby the Nords who have settled in Starck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.63,0:13:25.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have staved off invasion\Nby offering them money and goods,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.93,0:13:28.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but it won't be long\Nbefore our coffers are depleted.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.39,0:13:31.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Before that comes to pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.14,0:13:35.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,shouldn't our first order of business be\Nto bolster our current regime
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.31,0:13:38.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,under Sir Lassic, and take on Milza?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.27,0:13:39.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.69,0:13:42.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're absolutely right about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.86,0:13:47.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I, too, agree that now is not the time\Nfor our leadership to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.03,0:13:55.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And just as Sir Alfred mentioned earlier, I am\Nto blame for the deaths of so many Lords.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.83,0:13:57.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's acknowledging it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.21,0:14:06.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For that reason, I hereby vow to invade Altirk,\Nand bring down Milza, the prince of Dartania!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.18,0:14:13.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I can't do that on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.27,0:14:16.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to ask for your assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.39,0:14:22.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Theo, are you saying that you'll lead the charge\Nto defeat Prince Milza, and regain Altirk?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.53,0:14:28.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As long as I have the approval\Nof Sir Villar's younger brother, Selge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.20,0:14:33.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not capable of defeating Milza.\NI'm well aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.20,0:14:34.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's acknowledging it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.66,0:14:37.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, that's not the only reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.67,0:14:42.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Sir Selge has no objection,\NI assume there's no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.22,0:14:55.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Sir Theo, you're confident that\Nyou can defeat Milza in battle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.93,0:14:57.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have no confidence for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.06,0:15:02.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if I don't defeat Milza,\Nthe Treaty will have no future.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.40,0:15:06.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And it will also allow us\Nto carry out Sir Villar's legacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.87,0:15:19.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been quite a while,\Nbut I've baked some sweets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.54,0:15:22.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope that you find them to your liking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.39,0:15:36.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then, first of all,\Nyour conquest of Altirk was brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.14,0:15:40.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It took much longer than I'd anticipated,\Nand for that I am embarrassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.40,0:15:45.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those unfamiliar with Altirk's uniqueness\Nwill have their excuses,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.40,0:15:49.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but if it hadn't been you,\Nthey would've fled that land by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.03,0:15:53.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Not that it matters to the people\Nwho rule over them, though, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.70,0:15:57.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That's not true. Some rulers force their people\Ninto slavery, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.71,0:16:02.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But turning them into slaves\Nmakes it easier for them to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.00,0:16:05.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They become rebellious because they're given\Nsome semblance of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.96,0:16:09.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hear that the slaves are in revolt in Starck.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.18,0:16:13.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I may be the leader of the Alliance,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.64,0:16:17.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't intend to meddle with the Lords\Nregarding their management of their territories.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.68,0:16:21.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That said, I will not accept\Ninstability in any regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.94,0:16:25.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All the more so if that becomes the reason\Nwhy the Alliance is refused their cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.98,0:16:31.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Suppressing them by force\Nwill only breed ill will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.11,0:16:34.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Better to give it time,\Nand bring the disorder under control slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.33,0:16:39.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,While that's happening,\NI shall pry away Regalia and Haman.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.33,0:16:41.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Haman is my prey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.87,0:16:49.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once the battle with Earl Le Couleurs ends,\NI, too, plan to advance into Ozeri from Bulltava.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.21,0:16:50.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.05,0:16:56.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Earl of Nord has Bredland, the small continent\Nto the north, more or less in his clutches.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.81,0:16:58.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's sure to move on to the Union next.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.31,0:17:03.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Lords of the Union lack cohesion,\Nand therefore should be no match for Sir Erik.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.65,0:17:07.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, it's Theo Cornaro\Nwho has me worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.90,0:17:10.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That man will be aiming to liberate Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.74,0:17:13.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sooner or later, I will deal with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.16,0:17:16.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Don't underestimate the Union's ability\Nto muster troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.57,0:17:19.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}If the need arises,\Nplease request reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.12,0:17:25.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}You too, Lady Ulrika. No matter what situation\NStarck may be, I'd like you to respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.42,0:17:27.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.25,0:17:33.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}At any rate, the three of us need to join forces\Nto defeat the Altirk Treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.80,0:17:39.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Sweets, too, taste better in a gathering\Nlike this one, rather than partaken alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.94,0:17:51.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.36,0:17:57.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.41,0:18:02.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Theo Cornaro just declared his intent\Nto take back the Forest of Eternal Darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.54,0:18:07.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With your permission,\NI shall return to Altirk at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.17,0:18:10.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sir Milza?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.63,0:18:16.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever you do,\Ndon't misjudge Theo Cornaro's abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.76,0:18:18.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.10,0:18:24.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to take on Milza here in this forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.35,0:18:29.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll use this forest as our foothold\Nto defeat Milza, and then take back Altirk!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.90,0:18:40.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Dartania forces number 10,000 in all.\NCompared to that, we have 2,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.28,0:18:42.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we fight them head on,\Nwe have no chance of winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.91,0:18:45.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, we do have\Nthe geographical advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.46,0:18:48.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With its massive army,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.63,0:18:52.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dartania can't move freely throughout\Nthe heavily-wooded Forest of Eternal Darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.88,0:18:55.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and their mobility will also be impaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.01,0:19:01.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we fight in the Forest\Nof Eternal Darkness, we can win for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.01,0:19:02.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The issue is actually what comes after.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.56,0:19:07.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, we'll have to leave this forest,\Nand advance on Castle Unicorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.48,0:19:13.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But in order to seize Castle Unicorn with its\Nheavy defenses, several conditions must be met.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.48,0:19:16.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For starters, troops, I think?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.20,0:19:20.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll probably have to call on\Nall of the Altirk Treaty's forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.87,0:19:23.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Ideally, we'd gather\Na vast number of troops,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.70,0:19:27.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and seal the Dartanian forces\Ninside Castle Unicorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.58,0:19:32.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our leader, Lassic, is already working\Nto gather the entire Treaty army.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.92,0:19:35.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The other issue is enemy reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.42,0:19:40.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fortunately, Waldlind is currently battling\Nthe Earl of Le Couleurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.01,0:19:41.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and cannot spare any men\Nfrom their vast army.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.26,0:19:44.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What other nations can come to their aid?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.06,0:19:46.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dartania itself, and Starck.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.52,0:19:48.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding Dartania,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.98,0:19:54.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told that an anti-Milza faction has emerged,\Nso we are now seeking their cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.77,0:19:58.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rumor has it that in Starck,\Nthe slaves are in revolt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.74,0:19:59.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I've heard that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.32,0:20:03.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case,\Nwhat if we capitalize on that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.28,0:20:05.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to do just that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.16,0:20:08.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who should we send in?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.20,0:20:09.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.17,0:20:14.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My family, the Rossinis,\Nruled Sistina with tyranny.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.21,0:20:17.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know how to contain\Na rebellion by the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.09,0:20:20.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The opposite, too, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.09,0:20:23.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then can I impose on you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.30,0:20:25.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.85,0:20:31.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you have heard just now,\Nthat's the situation we're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.81,0:20:33.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know when we might falter,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.77,0:20:35.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and if that happens,\Nwe can't get back on our feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.90,0:20:39.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be like crossing a river on thin ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.90,0:20:42.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we have no choice but to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.49,0:20:48.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, Theo Cornaro has declared\Nhis intent to kill you, and liberate Altirk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.12,0:20:51.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His seizure of the Forest of Eternal Darkness\Nis just the first step.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.79,0:20:52.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seized?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.08,0:20:57.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After sneaking back the way he did,\Nhow dare he claim that he stole it from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.63,0:21:01.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're absolutely right,\Nbut since the death of Villar, the earl of Altirk,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.55,0:21:05.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,the Forest of Eternal Darkness\Nis your domain, Sir Milza.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.06,0:21:09.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can crush Theo with my eyes closed.\NWe're mobilizing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.02,0:21:11.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.60,0:21:13.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.06,0:21:15.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}It would be too risky to invade.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.98,0:21:18.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}We should wait for them to exit the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.19,0:21:21.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Do you think that I'll lose\Nto a nobody like Theo?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.74,0:21:24.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}In any other place but the Forest of\NEternal Darkness, you would never lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.12,0:21:27.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But a battle in that demon territory
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.12,0:21:29.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,would put our forces\Nat an overwhelming disadvantage!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.74,0:21:33.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And Theo Cornaro is a far more dangerous\Nopponent than you think—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.62,0:21:34.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.67,0:21:41.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have already offered my opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.38,0:21:44.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The decision is yours to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.43,0:21:46.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've already given you the order.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.43,0:21:49.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To invade the Forest of Eternal Darkness,\Nand kill Theo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.81,0:21:51.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Start your preparations at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.10,0:21:53.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.27,0:22:01.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you, Theo Cornaro. I'll make you regret\Nthrowing down the gauntlet at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.11,0:22:05.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,RETURN
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.04,0:23:40.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,EPISODE 16\NOUTPOST
